First, we need to write the given system of linear equations in matrix form Ax = b, where A is the matrix of coefficients, x is the column vector of variables, and b is the column vector of constants.

A = \begin{bmatrix}
2 & 3 & 4 \\
3 & 5 & 7 \\
4 & 7 & 10
\end{bmatrix}

x = \begin{bmatrix}
x \\
y \\
z
\end{bmatrix}

b = \begin{bmatrix}
20 \\
29 \\
38
\end{bmatrix}

Now, we will perform Cholesky decomposition on matrix A. We want to find a lower triangular matrix L such that A = LL^T.

L = \begin{bmatrix}
l_{11} & 0 & 0 \\
l_{21} & l_{22} & 0 \\
l_{31} & l_{32} & l_{33}
\end{bmatrix}

Using the Cholesky decomposition formulas:

l_{11} = \sqrt{a_{11}} = \sqrt{2}
l_{21} = a_{21}/l_{11} = 3/\sqrt{2}
l_{31} = a_{31}/l_{11} = 4/\sqrt{2}
l_{22} = \sqrt{a_{22} - l_{21}^2} = \sqrt{5 - (3/\sqrt{2})^2} = \sqrt{1}
l_{32} = (a_{32} - l_{21}l_{31})/l_{22} = (7 - (3/\sqrt{2})(4/\sqrt{2}))/1 = 1
l_{33} = \sqrt{a_{33} - l_{31}^2 - l_{32}^2} = \sqrt{10 - (4/\sqrt{2})^2 - 1^2} = \sqrt{2}

So, L = \begin{bmatrix}
\sqrt{2} & 0 & 0 \\
3/\sqrt{2} & 1 & 0 \\
4/\sqrt{2} & 1 & \sqrt{2}
\end{bmatrix}

Now, we will solve the system Ly = b for y:

\begin{bmatrix}
\sqrt{2} & 0 & 0 \\
3/\sqrt{2} & 1 & 0 \\
4/\sqrt{2} & 1 & \sqrt{2}
\end{bmatrix}
\begin{bmatrix}
y_1 \\
y_2 \\
y_3
\end{bmatrix} =
\begin{bmatrix}
20 \\
29 \\
38
\end{bmatrix}

Solving this system, we get:

y_1 = 20/\sqrt{2} = 10\sqrt{2}
y_2 = (29 - 3/\sqrt{2} * 10\sqrt{2}) = -1
y_3 = (38 - 4/\sqrt{2} * 10\sqrt{2} - 1) / \sqrt{2} = 1\sqrt{2}

Now, we will solve the system L^Tx = y for x:

\begin{bmatrix}
\sqrt{2} & 3/\sqrt{2} & 4/\sqrt{2} \\
0 & 1 & 1 \\
0 & 0 & \sqrt{2}
\end{bmatrix}
\begin{bmatrix}
x \\
y \\
z
\end{bmatrix} =
\begin{bmatrix}
10\sqrt{2} \\
-1 \\
1\sqrt{2}
\end{bmatrix}

Solving this system, we get:

z = (1\sqrt{2})/\sqrt{2} = 1
y = -1 - z = -2
x = (10\sqrt{2} - 3/\sqrt{2} * (-2) - 4/\sqrt{2})/\sqrt{2} = 4

So, the solution to the given system of linear equations is:

x = 4
y = -2
z = 1
